@deepdiver1975 @icewind1991 :  customer is getting similar logs with smb mount when attempting to perform a sync from a mac client.  lets say they have a file called test.txt on the oc server.  they modify it on their mac and it syncs to the oc server.  they get the following in the logs:

{"app":"php","message":"filetype(): lstat failed for smb:\/\/xxxxx@x.x.x.x\/data\/users%2fnick%2ftest.txt at \/srv\/www\/htdocs\/owncloud\/apps\/files_external\/lib\/streamwrapper.php#33","level":2,"time":"2013-10-03t18:24:59+00:00"}
{"app":"php","message":"filetype(): lstat failed for smb:\/\/xxxxx@x.x.x.x\/data\/users%2fnick%2ftest.txt at \/srv\/www\/htdocs\/owncloud\/apps\/files_external\/lib\/streamwrapper.php#33","level":2,"time":"2013-10-03t18:25:00+00:00"}
{"app":"php","message":"stat(): stat failed for smb:\/\/xxxxx@x.x.x.x\/data\/users%2fnick%2ftest.txt at \/srv\/www\/htdocs\/owncloud\/apps\/files_external\/lib\/smb.php#65","level":2,"time":"2013-10-03t18:25:00+00:00"}


a new file of size 0 is created called test.txt.part and it never replaces test.txt and the updates are never made to test.txt.

do you think this is the same issue??

if so, what is the status on this fix?
